criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. 60 years old or older;

          2. five years or more of education and scores of MMSE ≥ 24 points;

          3. Chinese as their first language.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Alzheimer's dementia or Parkinson's dementia diagnosed according to DSM-IV;

          2. history of mental disorders (e.g., depression and schizophrenia) diagnosed according
             to DSM-IV;

          3. history of pre-existing cerebrovascular disorders;

          4. known diseases affecting the eye or optic nerve, e.g., glaucoma or increased
             intraocular pressure (IOP), retinal detachment, retinal degeneration;

          5. hyperglycemia (fasting blood glucose ≥ 7.0 mmol/L);

          6. unwillingness to comply with the protocol or procedures.
